    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Lincheng/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-24T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1923—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 24—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. Chinese authorities not informed.</p>
                <p>In accordance with resolution of diplomatic body consuls at Lincheng have been
                    instructed to convey following message to brigand chiefs: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“[Apparent omission] is delayed or withheld owing to the refusal of
                            brigands to accept reasonable terms offered to them by the Chinese
                            authorities. Foreign governments will hold brigands responsible with
                            their lives for any fatal consequences which may ensue to their
                            nationals as a result of such delay or refusal to treat.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0764" n="648" xml:id="pg_648"/>
                <p>Consuls have been instructed in making this communication to make it quite clear
                    to brigands that they are not authorized to enter into negotiations with them or
                    to give any form of guarantee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
